We can now consider $j_{t}$ and $k_{t}$ as a digit replacement dynamics going from the most significant digits of $x_{t}$ and $\mu$ to the less ones
\begin{eqnarray}
j_{t} &\equiv& \left \lfloor \log_{p} x_{t} \right \rfloor-t \\
k_{t} &\equiv& \left \lfloor \log_{p} \mu \right \rfloor-t
